---

<ToolLayout
  title="Username Generator - Gaming & Social Media | Webutilbox"
  description="Generate unique, creative usernames based on your name, interests, or keywords. Free online username generator with availability suggestions."
  canonical={canonical}
  ogImage="https://webutilbox.com/assets/og/og-text-tools.svg"
  keywords="username generator, random username, gaming names, cool usernames, name generator, discord names, instagram username ideas"
  h1="👤 Username Generator"
  subtitle="Generate unique, cool usernames for gaming, social media, and more. Find your perfect username!"
  lastUpdated=""
  shareText="Free%20online%20Username%20Generator%20on%20Webutilbox.%20Privacy-focused%2C%20runs%20100%25%20in%20your%20browser."
  shareUrl={canonical}
  embedUrl={canonical}
  embedTitle="Username Generator - Gaming & Social Media -- Webutilbox"
  embedHeight={600}
  toolCss={false}
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>

<div class="workspace">
            <div style="margin-bottom:20px">
                <label style="display:block;margin-bottom:10px;font-weight:600">Category:</label>
                <div class="category-grid">
                    <button class="category-btn active" onclick="setCategory('gaming')">?? Gaming</button>
                    <button class="category-btn" onclick="setCategory('cool')">?? Cool</button>
                    <button class="category-btn" onclick="setCategory('cute')">?? Cute</button>
                    <button class="category-btn" onclick="setCategory('aesthetic')">? Aesthetic</button>
                    <button class="category-btn" onclick="setCategory('funny')">?? Funny</button>
                    <button class="category-btn" onclick="setCategory('random')">?? Random</button>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="username-inputs">
                <div class="input-group">
                    <label>Length</label>
                    <input type="number" id="length" value="8" min="4" max="20" style="width:100%;padding:10px">
                </div>
                <div class="input-group">
                    <label>Count</label>
                    <input type="number" id="count" value="10" min="1" max="50" style="width:100%;padding:10px">
                </div>
            </div>
            <div style="display:flex;gap:10px;margin-bottom:15px;flex-wrap:wrap">
                <label style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;cursor:pointer">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="includeNumbers" checked>
                    <span style="font-size:0.9rem">Include numbers</span>
                </label>
                <label style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;cursor:pointer">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="includeUnderscore">
                    <span style="font-size:0.9rem">Include underscore</span>
                </label>
                <label style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;cursor:pointer">
                    <input type="checkbox" id="capitalize" checked>
                    <span style="font-size:0.9rem">Capitalize</span>
                </label>
            </div>
            <div class="button-group">
                <button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="generateUsernames()">Generate Usernames</button>
                <button class="btn btn-secondary" onclick="clearResults()">Clear</button>
            </div>
            <div id="results" style="display:none;margin-top:20px">
                <h3 style="color:var(--primary);margin-bottom:15px">Generated Usernames:</h3>
                <div id="usernameList"></div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Share Bar -->

<style>
.username-card{background:var(--light);padding:20px;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid var(--border);margin:10px 0;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:10px;transition:all 0.2s}
        .username-card:hover{border-color:var(--primary);transform:translateX(5px)}
        .username-text{font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--primary);word-break:break-all;flex:1}
        .username-copy-btn{flex-shrink:0}
        .category-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(150px,1fr));gap:10px;margin:15px 0}
        .category-btn{padding:12px;background:var(--light);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;cursor:pointer;text-align:center;transition:all 0.2s;white-space:nowrap}
        .category-btn:hover,.category-btn.active{border-color:var(--primary);background:var(--primary);color:var(--dark)}
        .username-inputs{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:15px;margin-bottom:15px}
        
        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .username-inputs{grid-template-columns:1fr}
            .username-card{padding:15px;flex-direction:column;align-items:stretch;gap:10px}
            .username-text{font-size:1.1rem;text-align:center}
            .username-copy-btn{width:100%}
            .category-grid{grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(120px,1fr));gap:8px}
            .category-btn{padding:10px;font-size:0.85rem}
        }
        
        @media (max-width: 480px) {
            .category-grid{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr)}
            .username-text{font-size:1rem}
        }
</style>


<script src="/js/username-generator.js" defer></script>

<div class="info-section" slot="info">
<h2>Username Generator - Create Unique Usernames for Gaming and Social Media</h2>
            <p>The Username Generator is a free tool that creates unique, creative usernames tailored to different styles and platforms. Whether you need a fierce gaming handle, a cute social media name, an aesthetic username for Instagram, or a funny alias for a forum, this tool generates dozens of options instantly based on your preferences. No signup required, and you can generate as many as you need.</p>

            <h3>What Is a Username Generator?</h3>
            <p>A username generator combines words, numbers, and formatting rules to produce original username ideas that match a particular style or vibe. Coming up with a good username on your own can be surprisingly difficult — the name needs to be memorable, available on the platform you want to use it on, and reflective of your personality or brand. A generator gives you a large pool of options to choose from, which makes finding the right one much faster.</p>
            <p>This tool uses curated word lists organized by category — Gaming, Cool, Cute, Aesthetic, Funny, and Random — to produce usernames that feel appropriate for each context. Gaming usernames tend to be bold and powerful, while aesthetic usernames lean toward elegant and evocative words. The Random category draws from all word lists for maximum variety.</p>
            <p>You can customize the output with options for length, quantity, number inclusion, underscore separators, and capitalization. Generate up to 50 usernames at once, then copy any one you like with a single click. If none of the first batch appeals to you, generate again for a completely new set.</p>

            <h3>Username Generation Options</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Six style categories: Gaming, Cool, Cute, Aesthetic, Funny, and Random for varied results</li>
                <li>Adjustable username length from 4 to 20 characters to match platform requirements</li>
                <li>Bulk generation of up to 50 usernames at once for maximum choice</li>
                <li>Optional number suffix to increase uniqueness and availability on crowded platforms</li>
                <li>Optional underscore separator between word components for a classic username style</li>
                <li>Capitalization toggle to start the username with an uppercase letter</li>
                <li>One-click copy button on each generated username for instant use</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>How to Use the Username Generator</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Step 1: Select a style category by clicking one of the category buttons (Gaming, Cool, Cute, Aesthetic, Funny, or Random)</li>
                <li>Step 2: Set your preferred username length using the Length input field</li>
                <li>Step 3: Set how many usernames to generate at once using the Count input field</li>
                <li>Step 4: Toggle the options — Include Numbers, Include Underscore, Capitalize — to match your preferences</li>
                <li>Step 5: Click "Generate Usernames" to produce your list</li>
                <li>Step 6: Click "Copy" next to any username you want to use</li>
                <li>Step 7: If you do not find one you like, click Generate again for a fresh batch</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Creating the Right Username</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Creating a new gaming tag for Xbox, PlayStation, Steam, or Epic Games when your preferred name is taken</li>
                <li>Finding a unique Instagram or TikTok username that fits your personal brand or aesthetic</li>
                <li>Generating a Discord username that stands out in servers and communities</li>
                <li>Coming up with a Reddit or forum alias that matches the tone of the community you are joining</li>
                <li>Creating a professional-sounding username for a new email address or work account</li>
                <li>Brainstorming brand names or handles for a new social media presence or content channel</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Choosing a Memorable Username</h3>
            <p>Keep your username short and easy to spell. Long or complex usernames are harder for others to remember, type, or tag in posts. Aim for something under 15 characters if possible, and avoid unusual character combinations that might be confusing when spoken aloud or typed on a mobile keyboard.</p>
            <p>Always check availability on the platform you intend to use before committing to a username. Even a generated name that seems unique might already be taken on popular platforms. Most platforms show availability in real time as you type during account creation, so have a few backup options ready from your generated list.</p>
            <p>Avoid including personal information like your real name, birth year, or location in your username, especially for public-facing accounts. A username that reveals personal details can be a privacy risk and also limits your flexibility if you want to use the same handle across multiple platforms over time.</p>

            

            <h3>Usernames Generated Client-Side Only</h3>
            <p>Generation runs in your browser. No preferences or usernames are transmitted.</p>
        
            <h3>Frequently Asked Questions</h3>
            <div class="faq-list">
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How are usernames generated?</button>
                    <div class="faq-answer"><p>Usernames are generated by combining adjectives, nouns, verbs, and numbers in various patterns. You can customize the style (funny, professional, gaming, etc.), include or exclude numbers, and set a maximum length. Each generation produces a new set of unique suggestions.</p></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What makes a good username?</button>
                    <div class="faq-answer"><p>A good username is memorable, easy to spell, not too long (under 20 characters), available across platforms, and reflects your personality or brand. Avoid using personal information like your real name, birth year, or location for privacy reasons.</p></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I check if a username is available?</button>
                    <div class="faq-answer"><p>This tool generates username ideas. To check availability, you will need to search on each platform individually. Some third-party tools like Namecheckr allow you to check availability across multiple platforms simultaneously.</p></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Should I use the same username everywhere?</button>
                    <div class="faq-answer"><p>Using the same username across platforms makes you easier to find and builds a consistent online identity. However, it also makes it easier to connect your accounts. For privacy, use different usernames on different platforms.</p></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What are good username styles for gaming?</button>
                    <div class="faq-answer"><p>Gaming usernames often combine a cool adjective with a noun or animal (ShadowWolf, IronFox), use alliteration (DarkDragon, SwiftStrike), include numbers for uniqueness (Phoenix99), or use a single memorable word. Avoid spaces since many platforms do not allow them.</p></div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="related-tools">
                <h3>Related Tools</h3>
                <div class="related-tools-grid">
                    <a href="../password-generator/" class="related-tool-link">Password Generator</a>
                    <a href="../instagram-bio-generator/" class="related-tool-link">Instagram Bio Generator</a>
                    <a href="../slug-generator/" class="related-tool-link">Slug Generator</a>
                    <a href="../random-string-generator/" class="related-tool-link">Random String Generator</a>
                    <a href="../lorem-ipsum/" class="related-tool-link">Lorem Ipsum Generator</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
</div>

</ToolLayout>